  "decision_conditions": [
    "<div><p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">The proposal, by reason of scale, siting, bulk and design, would be an undesirable addition which would result in a loss of symmetry across the terrace row and banjo cul de sac and would compromise the openness of the corner plot. It would also fail to respect, preserve or enhance the local distinctiveness of the Becontree Estate, particularly given its impact on a characteristic banjo cul de sac. As such, the proposal fails to respect or reflect the character of the host dwelling, terrace row and surrounding area, resulting in a harmful impact to each of these, as well as to the street scene,&nbsp;character and appearance of the banjo cul de sac. The proposed extension thus fails to accord with the following policies which seek to ensure good design which respects and reflects the character of the local area and is sympathetic to local character and history:</span></p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Paragraph 130 of the National Planning Policy Framework&nbsp;National Planning Policy Framework (NPPF) (DLUHC, 2021)</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Policies D4 and HC1 of the London Plan (March 2021)</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Policies CP2 and CP3 of the&nbsp;Local Development Framework (LDF) Core Strategy (July 2010)</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Policies BP2, BP8 and BP11 of the&nbsp;Local Development Framework (LDF) Borough Wide Development Plan Document (DPD) (March 2011)</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Sections 4.1 and 5.4&nbsp;of the Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (February 2012)</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Policies SP2, DMD4 and DMD6 of&nbsp;The London Borough of Barking and Dagenhamâ€™s Draft Local Plan: (Regulation 19 Submission Version, December 2021)</span></li></ul></div><div><br></div>"
